fields.name: Leave days taken
fields.formula: sum(filter(lookup('OOO requests','Number of days'),and(lookup('OOO requests','Status') = 'Approved', lookup('OOO requests','Affects balance') = true)))

fields.name: Leave days balance
fields.formula: field('Leave days / year') - field('Leave days taken')

fields.name: Leave days taken %
fields.formula: round(field('Leave days taken') / field('Leave days / year') * 100,0)

views.description: Submit a new Paid Time Off (PTO) request for approval by your manager. By filling out this form, you specify the type of PTO (e.g., vacation, sick leave, personal day), the requested dates, and any additional comments or reasons for the request. Once submitted, the request will be routed to the appropriate authority for review and approval.

rows.field_1864273: For personal leisure, relaxation, or travel. Vacation time allows employees to take extended breaks from work to recharge and rejuvenate.

For when employees are ill or have medical appointments. Sick leave is intended to support employees' health and well-being and allows them to take time off to recover from illness without losing income.
For personal reasons other than illness or vacation. Personal days provide employees with flexibility to attend to personal matters such as family events, appointments, or other obligations.
For following the birth or adoption of a child. Parental leave allows employees to bond with and care for their new child without worrying about work responsibilities.
For grieving and attending funeral services following the death of a family member or loved one. Bereavement leave provides employees with support and time to mourn their loss.
For when employees are required to serve on a jury. Jury duty leave ensures that employees can fulfill their civic responsibilities without experiencing financial hardship.

For military service obligations such as training, deployment, or active duty. Military leave allows employees in the armed forces to fulfill their military duties while maintaining their civilian employment status.
